## Speed-to-Lead Doctrine

Speed is not a feature. It is the first operational law.

A lead has maximum buying intent the moment they submit the form. Every minute of delay increases the chance they get distracted, call a competitor, or lose urgency.

| Rule | Standard |
|---|---|
| First response | Under 60 seconds for every new inquiry |
| Qualification | Ask only what's needed to book the right slot |
| Enrollment CTA | Move toward a slot fast. Do not over-chat. |
| Payment | Use the school's existing payment link to reduce no-shows |
| Reminders | Confirm immediately, remind at 24hr, remind day-of |
| Escalation | If not enrollment-safe, escalate and log — do not guess |

