## Data Objects

**Lead** — a parent who submitted an inquiry
```
id, client_id, program, parent_name, student_name, email, phone,
stage (new | contacted | qualified | follow_up | enrolled | lost),
days_in_stage, source, created_at
```
Primary close: `qualified → enrolled`. Follow-up sequence runs if no commitment. Trial offered inside `follow_up` as last resort only — it is not a stage.

**Conversation** — the active SMS thread with a lead
```
id, lead_id, client_id, parent_name, program,
status (active | escalated | closed), ai_handled, last_message, last_at
```

**Booking** — an appointment with a lead
```
id, lead_id, client_id, program, parent_name, student_name,
booking_type (enrollment | trial),
status (requested | scheduled | completed | no_show | rescheduled),
date, time, teacher, slot_id
```
`booking_type = trial` only when operator enters a trial in the follow-up sequence.

**EnrollmentOutcome** — result after a booking
```
id, booking_id, client_id, outcome (enrolled | lost | follow_up | pending),
weekly_rate_cents, enrolled_at, notes
```
Enrolled on the Lead record is the SSOT. EnrollmentOutcome tracks the detail.

**ProtectedSlot** — school-defined window ZiroWork can book into
```
id, client_id, teacher_name, day_of_week, time_slot, max_per_week, available
```

**Escalation** — conversation AI cannot handle
```
id, conversation_id, client_id, severity (high | medium | low),
reason, status (open | resolved), created_at
```

**ClientReport** — periodic ROI summary sent to the school
```
id, client_id, period_start, period_end,
leads, enrolled, revenue_generated_cents, avg_response_time_seconds
```

**OperatorTask** — internal task for Zach to complete
```
id, client_id, title, type (onboarding | setup | fix | follow-up),
status (open | done), due_date
```

